news.title: Kanpur development body to use DGNSS for demarcating its properties
news.para: KDA vice-chairman Arvind Singh after a presentation given on Friday by its developer directed to use this digital technology first in the New Kanpur City being developed by the Authority between Mainavati Road and Kalyanpur-Bithoor Road.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects Rs 152 crore property tax in FY23
news.para: Officials of the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) said one of the main reasons for the record property tax collection is that several new properties have been brought under the property tax net.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body budget: Focus on ongoing projects, no hike in property tax
news.para: The total expenditure of the civic body is pegged at Rs 4,922.5 crore while the expected revenue is Rs 4,925 crore. There will be no hike in the property tax yet again—18th year in a row.

news.title: Jaipur: JMC-G cracks whip on urban development tax defaulters
news.para: The corporation has identified around 85 properties in each zone so far where UD tax ranging from Rs 10,000 to up to Rs 1 lakh is pending. Most of these properties are in Malviya Nagar and Jagatpura zones.

news.title: Over 4,500 properties sealed in Ahmedabad for pending property tax dues
news.para: The tax and revenue department sealed 1,761 properties located in the west zone, the highest number of properties sealed zone wise. AMC said that 720 properties were sealed in the east zone and 739 in the north-west zone.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Handing over of five lakh houses likely by March-end
news.para: The officials told chief minister Y S Jagan Mohan Reddy on Friday that works are in progress to complete the infrastructure as well for these houses.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body postpones plot auctions
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation-owned plots were to be auctioned at a cumulative base price of Rs 499.72 crore. Now with the standoff between the state revenue department and the developers, not many showed interest in participating in the auction, which was to be held on February 14.

news.title: Panchkula civic body sends notices of Rs 16 crore tax dues to seven government departments
news.para: The civic body has to collect Rs 15.7 crore from these departments, which have been served notices under sections 95 and 130 of the Haryana Municipal Corporation Act, 1974. The departments concerned will have to deposit tax in 15 days, failing which the process of sealing will be initiated.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Computerised draw held for CIDCO's mass housing scheme
news.para: ​​As per the scheme, 7,849 affordable Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) houses will be allotted to economically weaker section (EWS) in Ulwe node, he said.

news.title: Pune civic body not to hike property tax in next financial year
news.para: "Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) will not increase the levy this year. Tax slabs will remain the same," PMC administrator Vikram Kumar said.

news.title: RWAs demand structural audit of Delhi-NCR highrises
news.para: On Friday, the residents’ body shot a letter to Union urban development minister Hardeep Singh Puri stating that since NCR comes under seismic zone 4, which is a high-damage risk zone, the government should make necessary amendments in the Central Building Rules and make structural audits mandatory of all buildings before allowing possession.

news.title: UP-RERA imposes Rs 1.4 crore fine on 13 developers for violating orders, delays
news.para: “The UP-Rera has also directed erring promoters to submit a compliance report with its orders and deposit the penalty within 30 days, failing which the Authority will recover the cost from the arrears of land revenue,” added the official.

news.title: A H Wadia Trust sells 5.5-acre land parcel to hotel group for Rs 71 crore in Mumbai
news.para: According to CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, the transaction was registered on February 3, 2023, and a stamp duty of Rs 10.70 crore was paid by the buyer.

news.title: Gurugram: Promised in 2021, but flats still not handed over to buyers, builder may face action
news.para: The affordable housing project was launched in 2017 by the builder and the buyers were promised possession in 2021. The deadline was extended to 2023 in view of the pandemic.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body demolishes four 'illegal' structures in zone-D
news.para: Action was taken against three buildings in Model Town Extension and one in Model Town Gol Market, as they were in violation of building bylaws. The illegal portions of these buildings have been razed.
